title: For Sale:  Glock 19 Gen 4
postcontent:
I'm selling my Glock 19 Gen 4. I have put approximately 500 rounds through the gun. Please note that this is one of the early Gen 4's, the recoil spring is brand new (has approximately 200 rounds through it) and the ejector is the most recent version (the original ejector for the Gen 4's had issues with brass ejecting and hitting you in the face. This issue was fixed with the 30274 ejector, which is what is installed in this gun).
The gun comes with:
- Original case
- 3 magazines (two 15 rounds magazines and one 17 round magazine
- Glock 19 (duh)

PLEASE NOTE: As you can see the photos below, the gun has trudot night sights. The tritium in these is dead, so they are basically now just basic three dot sights. They work well and I preferred the three dot sights to the standard plastic glock sights, so I traded with a friend when he was going to be throwing his old sights away (the trudots are steel sights, while the original glock sights were plastic). The condition of the gun can be seen in the pictures. The inside of the gun is in very good condition (since I've only put 500 rounds through it, this should be obvious. I am a bit OCD about cleaning the gun, so it was cleaned at least once per month, regardless of whether it was shot or not). Note that I put 500 rounds through the gun, but I had bought it in near-perfect condition used from a gunstore. The gun had no notable wear on it (aside from a couple minor scratches on the back of the plastic cover at the rear of the slide), so I'm assuming the previous owner didn't like the gun and sold it before putting any significant amount of rounds through the gun. (My theory: he didn't know that glock had recalled the extractor, so he was getting hit in the face with brass and promptly sold the gun out of irritation... I replaced the extractor as soon as I got it and the gun no longer has that issue)....

I WILL REQUIRE TEXAS ID. CHL PREFERRED, BUT NOT NECESSARY. I WILL NEED YOU TO SIGN A BILL OF SALE. THIS IS NOT NEGOTIABLE.

Please text REDACTED if you are interested.

title: For Sale:  german mauser
postcontent: German WW2 sniper rifle- I have an original WW2 Mauser sniper rifle. This does not include the single claw scope mount, and ZF-39 scope. There aren’t any import marks, either, indicating the rifle came into the country prior to 1968. The mounting holes are soft soldered plugged, which is what Germany had to do to “de-mil” a certain number of sniper rifles, after the war. This one is dated 1917, Danzig, and is Gew. 98. This rifle was cut down to a K98 sometime in WW2, and fitted to a CZ24 stock, and mounted with the ZF-39 single claw scope mount. This rifle is in great condition, and shoots wonderfully with good ammo. I can include pics and the research is available to anyone interested, as it was to me, so just dig around, and you will find the exact same info, easily. Im asking $450.
